thread.title: Ohio State remains No. 1 in AP poll after close call against Indiana
thread.title_full: Ohio State remains No. 1 in AP poll after close call against Indiana

author: Associated Press
title: Ohio State remains No. 1 in AP poll after close call against Indiana
text:
Ohio State remains No. 1 in AP poll after close call against Indiana Ohio State at Indiana Chris Russell / Columbus Dispatch 
Cornerback Eli Apple (13) knocks the ball away from Indiana receiver Ricky Jones Jr. on the last play of the game to preserve Ohio State's 34-27 victory on Saturday. 
Cornerback Eli Apple (13) knocks the ball away from Indiana receiver Ricky Jones Jr. on the last play of the game to preserve Ohio State's 34-27 victory on Saturday. (Chris Russell / Columbus Dispatch) Associated Press 
Ohio State remained No. 1 in the Associated Press college football top 25 and tied a poll record Sunday, despite lagging support from the voters. 
Meanwhile, No. 2 Texas Christian and No. 3 Baylor edged forward, No. 4 Michigan State slipped and No. 5 Utah and No. 6 Clemson took big jumps. 
After four top-10 teams lost on Saturday, the rankings were rattled and five teams received first-place votes. The Buckeyes received 38 first-place votes, their fewest this season after beginning as the first unanimous preseason No. 1. TCU has five first-place votes, Baylor received 10, Utah has seven and No. 9 Texas A&M has one. 
Ohio State was the only team in the top 16 to have the same ranking this week as last. 
The Buckeyes held off Indiana, 34-27, on Saturday and have now been top-ranked 101 times, matching Oklahoma for the most in the 79-year history of the media poll. 
Georgia QB keeps job 
Georgia Coach Mark Richt says he's sticking with Greyson Lambert as the Bulldogs' starting quarterback. 
Lambert completed just 10 of 24 passes for 86 yards in a 38-10 loss to Alabama. Brice Ramsey also got some playing time, but he completed only one pass and had two interceptions. 
Receiver Isaiah McKenzie (left hamstring) and center Brandon Kublanow (sprained ankle) are questionable for Saturday's game against Tennessee. Georgia (4-1, 2-1 Southeastern Conference) plunged from eighth to No. 19 in the latest Associated Press rankings. 
Surgery for Spartan 
Michigan State defensive back RJ Williamson will miss an extended period of time after having surgery Sunday on a torn biceps. 
Williamson, a fifth-year senior, has intercepted two passes this season for the fourth-ranked Spartans. 
Michigan State plays at Rutgers on Saturday night.
